MAC terminal shortcut and Github Installation
1) Open Launchpad from your Dock or with the keyboard shortcut Fn + F4.
2) Type “Terminal” into the search box at the top.
3) When the Terminal icon displays, click it.
--------------------------------------------
Press Cmd + Space to open Spotlight search, and type terminal and hit return.
----------------------------------------------------
Github steps:
Copy & paste the following into the terminal window and hit Return.
1. /bin/bash -c "$(curl -fsSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Homebrew/install/master/install.sh)"
Press Enter
After getting password message to enter login password (you have to keep typing the password as the
password will not visible )
You will get Press RETRUN message,
Press Enter
After getting password message to enter login password (you have to keep typing the password as the
password will not visible )
After completion of download enter the following command.
2. brew install git
3. git --version
You can use Git now.

---------------------------
configuration
---------------------------
git config --global user.name "your github user name"
git config --global user.email "your github email"

pwd-present working directory(to know the current path)
cd(change directory)- to move/open to a paticular folder
mkdir <name_directory>- to create a new folder
cd.. -come out of a directory 
ls- list of files

git clone <git link>
git status 
git add <file_name>
git commit -m "<message>"
